This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on multilingual masked language modeling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of transfer learning and the discovery of universal latent symmetries in learned embedding spaces, which are topics that are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of text from different domains, which could potentially involve computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for processing visual data.
